    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>@ hides error message and make it ignored by PHP's error_log mechanism.</p>

<p>Details:
PHP Fatal error:  Allowed memory size of 16777216 bytes exhausted (tried to allocate 275863 bytes) in lib/Zend/Pdf/Filter/Compression/Flate.php on line 52
It's not being displayed nor logged using standard PHP error_log mechanism, it is just silent fail hard to debug.
I get this error on php.ini "memory_limit = 16M" (debian's default) so this error can occur quite often. 
@ should not be used when function can generate fatal err, and if case of gzcompress() it can happen often.</p>

